TITLE: Satellite imagery venture Planet delivers record quarter, sees annual revenue nearing $200 million
SUMMARY: Planet delivered record results for the third quarter and forecast nearly $200 million in annual revenue.

TITLE: Adobe stock climbs on a more profitable quarter than predicted
SUMMARY: The design software company saw revenue growth slow sequentially, including in the key Creative category. But it maintained full-year guidance from October.

TITLE: Olive Garden parent company Darden beats estimates, raises outlook
SUMMARY: Darden Restaurants, the parent company of Olive Garden and LongHorn Steakhouse, raised its outlook for the year.

TITLE: Nike surges after results top expectations and retailer shows inventory progress
SUMMARY: Nike reported fiscal second-quarter earnings after the bell Tuesday.

TITLE: FedEx plans more cost cuts as soft demand hurts profits
SUMMARY: FedEx said it will be able to cut another $1 billion in costs beyond what it previously forecast.

TITLE: Semiconductor maker Micron announces 10% staff reduction, suspends bonuses
SUMMARY: Micron said it would hit its reduction target through voluntary departures as well as layoffs.
